Windows Vista (2007)

* Released: 2007
* Based on NT 6.0 kernel
* Editions: Home Basic, Home Premium, Business, Ultimate, Enterprise
* Major focus on security and system stability
* Introduced User Account Control (UAC)
* New graphical interface: **Aero** (glass effects, animations)
* Improved search and file indexing
* New driver model (WDDM) for better hardware support
* Enhanced networking and Wi-Fi management
* Better memory and process management than XP
* Higher hardware requirements compared to XP

Professional notes:

* Early versions had performance and driver compatibility issues
* Service Packs significantly improved stability and speed
* Laid the foundation for later systems like Windows 7
* Rarely used today, mainly for legacy or testing purposes

